What we can learn and adapt from RedMatic-HomeKit + paramsets.json

A. BLIND: only bidcos (channeltype BLIND) is working, hmip BLIND_VIRTUAL_TRANSCEIVER device isnt generated.

B. Auto choose matter device type by channel rega name
if channel name contains "licht" or "light" or "lampe" choose matter light for SWITCH channels
if channel name contains "standby" or "plug" or "steckdose" choose matter outlet for SWITCH channel

1. BLIND: ACTIVITY_STATE / DIRECTION → WindowCovering.operationalStatus
RedMatic subscribes to a separate datapoint (ACTIVITY_STATE on HmIP, DIRECTION on classic BidCos) and maps it to the WindowCovering position state (increasing / decreasing / stopped). We currently ignore this. It should be subscribed and applied to the WindowCovering cluster's operational status so controllers show a "moving" indicator.

Values:

ACTIVITY_STATE / DIRECTION: 0 = stopped, 1 = opening (INCREASING), 2 = closing (DECREASING)
2. Venetian blinds (BLIND_VIRTUAL_RECEIVER) — tilt via LEVEL_2
BLIND_VIRTUAL_RECEIVER channels have a second level datapoint LEVEL_2 (0.0–1.0) for slat tilt. SHUTTER_VIRTUAL_RECEIVER channels do not. RedMatic uses putParamset({LEVEL, LEVEL_2}) to set both atomically and maps LEVEL_2 to HomeKit's TargetVerticalTiltAngle ((value * 180) - 90 → °). Matter's WindowCovering cluster has a matching tilt lift attribute.

We need to: detect BLIND_VIRTUAL_RECEIVER type vs SHUTTER_VIRTUAL_RECEIVER in resolveChannelsForMatter and flag tilt support accordingly; subscribe and write LEVEL_2; use putParamset instead of individual setValue for blind actuators.

3. New channel types to add
Homematic channel type	Datapoint(s)	Matter cluster	Notes
MOTION_DETECTOR	MOTION (bool)	occupancySensor	widely deployed; HM-Sec-MDIR, HmIP-SMI/SMO
MOTION_DETECTOR	ILLUMINATION (float, lux)	lightSensor	optional alongside motion
TEMPERATURE_HUMIDITY_TRANSMITTER	ACTUAL_TEMPERATURE, HUMIDITY	temperatureSensor + humiditySensor	HM-WDS40-TH-I, HmIP-STH/STHD
THERMALCONTROL_TRANSMIT / CLIMATECONTROL_RT_TRANSCEIVER	ACTUAL_TEMPERATURE, SET_POINT_TEMPERATURE, CONTROL_MODE, LEVEL	thermostat	TRV and wall thermostats; complex bidirectional
SMOKE_DETECTOR	SMOKE_DETECTOR_ALARM_STATUS	smokeCOAlarm	HmIP-SWSD; SMOKE_DETECTOR_TEST_RESULT for fault state
ALARMSTATE devices (flood/water)	ALARMSTATE	waterFreeze / WaterLeak cluster	HmIP-SWD
POWERMETER	POWER, ENERGY_COUNTER, STATE	onOffOutlet + power measurement	HM-ES-PMSw1, HmIP-PSM
WEATHER	TEMPERATURE, HUMIDITY, WIND_SPEED, BRIGHTNESS, RAIN_COUNTER	Multiple sensors	HM-WDS100-C6-O; expose sub-sensors per datapoint
4. Channel address conventions confirmed
Status/battery datapoints always on channel :0: LOW_BAT, UNREACH, OPERATING_VOLTAGE, SABOTAGE, ERROR_CODE
Classic BidCos uses LOWBAT (no underscore); HmIP uses LOW_BAT
OPERATING_VOLTAGE on HmIP channel :0 can be mapped to a percentage (battery level)
We should extend the UNREACH/battery logic in discoverDevices to also subscribe to OPERATING_VOLTAGE on HmIP devices and map it to the battery percentage (RedMatic converts: value - 2.0) / (3.0 - 2.0) * 100).

5. putParamset vs setValue for blinds
RedMatic always uses putParamset (not setValue) when writing LEVEL+LEVEL_2 atomically for blind channels. We currently use setValue for LEVEL alone. For venetian blinds this is required; for simple shutters it might also be safer.

6. Power meter SWITCH — Outlet service with power measurement
The HM-ES-PMSw1 / HMIP-PSM devices expose POWER on a separate channel. RedMatic assigns OutletInUse to POWER > 0. We could expose a Matter onOffOutlet device and additionally surface a ElectricalEnergyMeasurement or ElectricalPowerMeasurement cluster.

7. HM-Sec-RHS / HmIP-SRH (window handle sensor) — 3-state contact
STATE = 0 (closed), 1 (tilted), 2 (open). No direct Matter equivalent. Can be exposed as a contact sensor (0 = closed, else open)



Priority order for next implementations
BLIND HMIP
BLIND ACTIVITY_STATE subscription → operationalStatus (low effort, high correctness)
Venetian blind tilt (LEVEL_2, BLIND_VIRTUAL_RECEIVER detection, putParamset)
MOTION_DETECTOR → occupancySensor (very common hardware, straightforward)
TEMPERATURE_HUMIDITY_TRANSMITTER → temperatureSensor + humiditySensor (very common)
SMOKE_DETECTOR → smokeCOAlarm
THERMOSTAT (complex, needs CONTROL_MODE, SET_POINT_TEMPERATURE, LEVEL for valve state)
